Aching with the need to break free<br>
Like a charmed creature...<br>
like the undead to a heretic...<br>
like the elemental with her Mage ... I followed</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
He did not tell me...<br>
<br>
of the sheer agony of this rebirth<br>
of the blinding brightness of this world<br>
of the incredible coldness of the air<br>
of the imbalance of these foreign wings<br>
of the naked shame I feel<br>
of this new heart that beats so fast in my breast<br>
<br>
<br>
He did not tell me...<br>
<br>
that I would stumble and fall<br>
these wings, so terrifying<br>
their color, too intense, blinding me<br>
leaving me with no balance<br>
too weak to carry me away<br>
body too fragile, shivering scared<br>
<br>
<br>
He did not tell me...<br>
<br>
I would turn and see the evidence of my rebirth<br>
how I would want to gather the shattered pieces<br>
try to crawl back inside<br>
sealing myself away from this unfamiliarity<br>
where I was bound tight, safe and secure<br>
now, I have nothing holding me, but his tender embrace<br>
<br>
<br>
He said...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">I cannot go back, never to return<br>
that I needed to be free and find the balance <br>
that the Goddess grants all with her love<br>
he holds me tightly, locking me with the spell of his eyes<br>
